709
01:01:11,630 --> 01:01:16,530
<i>The doctor said you've made a lot of improvement.</i><br>What great news!

710
01:01:18,450 --> 01:01:21,810
Even though the doctor has already reduced my dosage,

711
01:01:21,810 --> 01:01:26,350
if I had to go back to work right now,

712
01:01:26,350 --> 01:01:31,120
to be honest, I'm not sure I could do it.

713
01:01:31,120 --> 01:01:33,930
But life is like that.

714
01:01:33,930 --> 01:01:36,100
I think you used to push yourself too far.

715
01:01:36,100 --> 01:01:40,240
Don't you think it's a good thing to relax a bit<br>when you have this chance?

716
01:01:40,240 --> 01:01:41,980
In fact, I'm quite happy,

717
01:01:41,980 --> 01:01:44,690
because you have more time to be with me now.

718
01:01:44,690 --> 01:01:50,570
I actually hope your vacation can go even longer.

719
01:01:54,600 --> 01:01:56,200
Katy.

720
01:01:58,520 --> 01:02:03,790
Thank you, for never giving up on me.

721
01:02:06,250 --> 01:02:10,770
Without your being by my side and<br>supporting me unconditionally,

722
01:02:12,420 --> 01:02:14,910
I don't know how I would have turned out.

723
01:02:18,320 --> 01:02:20,860
This is just how love should be.

724
01:02:20,860 --> 01:02:27,580
Besides… being able to stay next to you makes me feel... very happy.

725
01:02:29,040 --> 01:02:36,970
<i>Subtitles brought to you by The Royal Team @ Viki</i>

726
01:02:39,950 --> 01:02:44,270
<i>♫ I want to build a whole new different world. ♫ </i>

727
01:02:44,270 --> 01:02:48,900
<i>♫ I welcome you, welcome you to experience it. ♫ </i>

728
01:02:53,810 --> 01:02:55,550
<i>Daddy.</i>

729
01:03:05,030 --> 01:03:07,390
Do you still see me as your dad?

730
01:03:08,950 --> 01:03:11,000
I'm sorry, Daddy.

731
01:03:11,000 --> 01:03:12,800
Would you please stop being mad?

732
01:03:13,770 --> 01:03:15,380
<i>General Manager Zhao.</i>

733
01:03:17,570 --> 01:03:19,710
What are you doing here?

734
01:03:19,710 --> 01:03:22,720
This is my private place. Please get out.

735
01:03:25,730 --> 01:03:28,420
Let me get straight to the point then.

736
01:03:28,420 --> 01:03:32,410
I want to marry Katy.<br>Please give us your blessing.

737
01:03:39,690 --> 01:03:43,580
Where did you get your confidence from?

738
01:03:43,580 --> 01:03:46,330
Wasn't it enough how you humiliated me<br> in the board meeting?

739
01:03:46,330 --> 01:03:51,590
You found a fishmonger to be my boss!<br>Now? What are you trying to do?

740
01:03:51,590 --> 01:03:55,240
You want me to let you marry my daughter?

741
01:03:55,970 --> 01:03:58,290
Who do you think you are?

742
01:04:00,470 --> 01:04:02,590
During the board meeting,

743
01:04:02,590 --> 01:04:08,080
I was simply presenting my standpoint as a CEO.

744
01:04:08,080 --> 01:04:10,330
I had no intention to show you disrespect.

745
01:04:12,140 --> 01:04:16,370
Besides, when that fishmonger was the CEO,

746
01:04:16,370 --> 01:04:19,530
everyone could see what a good job he did.

747
01:04:19,530 --> 01:04:21,190
Liu Wen Bin also said,

748
01:04:21,190 --> 01:04:23,290
about our company's affairs, big or small,

749
01:04:23,290 --> 01:04:25,560
no one knows them better than you do.

750
01:04:26,550 --> 01:04:31,440
Therefore, while he stands in as CEO,

751
01:04:31,440 --> 01:04:34,150
he'll definitely consult your opinions.

752
01:04:37,170 --> 01:04:39,980
As to Katy and I...

753
01:04:39,980 --> 01:04:45,610
If you would let her marry me,<br>will it still be necessary to say whom Yi Shan belongs to?

754
01:04:49,020 --> 01:04:53,850
However, even if you oppose,

755
01:04:53,850 --> 01:04:55,870
I will still marry her.

756
01:05:02,280 --> 01:05:07,670
Is your face made of elephant skin?<br><i>(meaning "very thick-skinned)</i>

757
01:05:09,010 --> 01:05:11,350
You really think you're a prince?

758
01:05:11,350 --> 01:05:14,280
Can Katy only marry you?

759
01:05:15,300 --> 01:05:18,510
Where did you get all that confidence from?

760
01:05:21,560 --> 01:05:26,520
Daddy. William really loves me.

761
01:05:27,490 --> 01:05:31,380
In my whole life, I'll only love him too.

762
01:05:33,330 --> 01:05:36,240
Can't you just give us your blessing?

763
01:05:36,240 --> 01:05:38,900
What are you talking about?

764
01:05:40,550 --> 01:05:42,960
Daddy.

765
01:05:42,960 --> 01:05:44,030
Dad.

766
01:05:44,030 --> 01:05:46,060
Don't call me that!

767
01:05:50,580 --> 01:05:54,700
You… watched me growing up since I was little.

768
01:05:54,700 --> 01:05:57,130
As my father has passed away,

769
01:05:57,130 --> 01:05:59,760
and Katy is your only child.

770
01:05:59,760 --> 01:06:02,490
I really love her very much.

771
01:06:02,490 --> 01:06:06,930
So… I will treat you as my own father.

772
01:06:08,270 --> 01:06:12,480
You'll be the host of our wedding.

773
01:06:12,480 --> 01:06:15,100
We will try to respect your

774
01:06:17,160 --> 01:06:21,710
You're lucky that I haven't kicked you out of here.

775
01:06:21,710 --> 01:06:24,550
What wedding?

776
01:06:24,550 --> 01:06:27,610
I haven't agreed yet. What wedding?

777
01:06:30,700 --> 01:06:33,090
Enough, Daddy.

778
01:06:37,210 --> 01:06:40,460
You know William and I have been through a lot.

779
01:06:40,460 --> 01:06:43,480
Now we're getting married.

780
01:06:43,480 --> 01:06:46,310
Can't you just feel happy for me?

781
01:06:46,310 --> 01:06:49,730
You silly girl. What's there to be happy about?

782
01:06:49,730 --> 01:06:52,530
- Daddy…<br>- Why are you talking about getting married?

783
01:06:54,460 --> 01:06:57,390
Dad. I'd like to toast to you.

784
01:06:57,390 --> 01:06:59,420
Don't call me that.

785
01:07:05,340 --> 01:07:07,230
Daddy.

786
01:07:11,960 --> 01:07:18,610
Are you going to let me walk into the wedding by myself<br>without anyone holding my hand?

787
01:07:18,610 --> 01:07:24,310
If I have to walk down the aisle alone, I'll be so wretched.

788
01:07:26,840 --> 01:07:31,650
My biggest dream is to have you,

789
01:07:31,650 --> 01:07:36,320
the person who loves me the most,

790
01:07:36,320 --> 01:07:39,720
hand me to the man I love.

791
01:07:42,840 --> 01:07:45,350
Can't you grant me this wish?

792
01:07:49,180 --> 01:07:54,700
Don't cry. You…<br>I can't bear to see you cry.

793
01:08:15,350 --> 01:08:17,970
Ok, ok...

794
01:08:23,150 --> 01:08:26,770
Are you sure he is William Yi, not Liu Wen Bin?

795
01:08:29,740 --> 01:08:32,600
Of course he is William.<br>I won't make the same mistake again.

796
01:08:32,600 --> 01:08:34,360
But you did make the mistake last time.

797
01:08:34,360 --> 01:08:36,050
I know I did, but not anymore.

798
01:08:36,050 --> 01:08:38,000
You'd better not mix it up again.

799
01:09:01,510 --> 01:09:05,670
Auntie. How are you feeling? Are you tired?

800
01:09:05,670 --> 01:09:10,230
Not at all. It has only been a short walk.

801
01:09:10,230 --> 01:09:13,520
I am supposed to take walks often anyway.

802
01:09:13,520 --> 01:09:16,220
Otherwise, being trapped in the house everyday

803
01:09:16,220 --> 01:09:17,990
and not being allowed to do any work,

804
01:09:17,990 --> 01:09:21,520
I'd feel like I'm going to get sick.

805
01:09:22,550 --> 01:09:25,760
I understand. This is how a patient feels.

806
01:09:25,760 --> 01:09:30,640
All day long you're being watched. <br>You're not allowed to do this, and not allowed to do that.

807
01:09:30,640 --> 01:09:33,340
Very annoying.

808
01:09:33,340 --> 01:09:37,650
Actually, you really don't need to come and spend time with me.

809
01:09:37,650 --> 01:09:42,580
I already told Ah Bin I can live alone. No problem.

810
01:09:42,580 --> 01:09:47,070
If you have things to take care of, just go ahead.<br>Don't worry about me.

811
01:09:47,070 --> 01:09:50,690
Right now, I'm not busy at all.

812
01:09:50,690 --> 01:09:53,590
The one who is busy working is Ah Bin.

813
01:09:54,610 --> 01:09:58,980
I'm enjoying my life, and I feel very content.

814
01:09:58,980 --> 01:10:01,980
Auntie, thank you.

815
01:10:03,020 --> 01:10:06,320
Thank you for making Ah Bin agree to help me.

816
01:10:07,470 --> 01:10:10,260
Stonehead. Ah Bin said

817
01:10:10,260 --> 01:10:14,530
you were the one who told him to cancel the development plan.

818
01:10:14,530 --> 01:10:18,200
Do you know? As soon as you halted the development,

819
01:10:18,200 --> 01:10:23,600
the county government immediately stopped<br>the expropriation plan.

820
01:10:23,620 --> 01:10:25,570
I really want to thank you.

821
01:10:25,570 --> 01:10:29,210
Thank you for letting the sea and the houses here

822
01:10:29,210 --> 01:10:32,610
be preserved.

823
01:10:32,610 --> 01:10:36,340
That project… shouldn't have been planned to begin with.

824
01:10:37,330 --> 01:10:40,830
The coast of Mei Village really is very beautiful.

825
01:10:40,830 --> 01:10:46,430
If a hotel resort is built, the coast<br>won't belong to everyone anymore.

826
01:10:48,020 --> 01:10:52,070
Actually, we don't need to

827
01:10:52,070 --> 01:10:54,660
keep things we like to ourselves.

828
01:10:54,660 --> 01:10:59,560
Let things stay the way they are,<br>don't spoil them,

829
01:10:59,560 --> 01:11:04,280
and just simply admire them.<br>That is the more correct attitude.

830
01:11:04,280 --> 01:11:08,910
Stonehead, you really have changed.

831
01:11:09,900 --> 01:11:13,980
That's all because of auntie.

832
01:11:15,390 --> 01:11:18,660
That's strange. I didn't give you candies to eat.

833
01:11:18,660 --> 01:11:20,860
How come you can say so many sweet words?

834
01:11:20,860 --> 01:11:25,560
How about this? Tell me what you want for dinner.<br>I'll cook for you.

835
01:11:25,560 --> 01:11:28,540
No way. You can't get too tired.

836
01:11:28,540 --> 01:11:30,380
I will cook for you instead.

837
01:11:32,490 --> 01:11:35,490
Really. It's not that I like to praise you.

838
01:11:35,490 --> 01:11:39,400
Your cooking skill is getting better and better.

839
01:11:39,400 --> 01:11:42,920
Last time the stirred fried salted fish rice you made,

840
01:11:42,920 --> 01:11:45,970
it tasted better than Ah Bin's.

841
01:11:47,000 --> 01:11:51,760
Of course. My cooking skill was better than<br>Ah Bin's from the start.

842
01:11:51,760 --> 01:11:55,590
Ah Bin...<br>What does he know?<i>(In Taiwanese)</i>

843
01:11:55,590 --> 01:11:58,560
Showing off your Taiwanese now? Beautiful!

844
01:12:03,660 --> 01:12:06,970
Stonehead, do you smell something?

845
01:12:08,600 --> 01:12:10,180
I think I do smell something.

846
01:12:10,180 --> 01:12:11,430
<i>Help!</i>

847
01:12:11,430 --> 01:12:13,550
<i>I burned my hair again!</i>

848
01:12:13,550 --> 01:12:14,970
What happened to you?

849
01:12:14,970 --> 01:12:17,940
Sorry, Auntie. I burned another pot of yours again.

850
01:12:17,940 --> 01:12:20,000
But that's ok. I have a lot of pots at my house.

851
01:12:20,000 --> 01:12:21,410
I will definitely buy you a new one.

852
01:12:21,410 --> 01:12:23,970
That's ok. Don't worry about the burned pot.

853
01:12:23,970 --> 01:12:25,690
But did your hands get burned?

854
01:12:25,690 --> 01:12:27,990
No. I'm ok.

855
01:12:31,290 --> 01:12:32,810
Are you alright?

856
01:12:32,810 --> 01:12:37,760
I'm alright, but the kitchen is not.

857
01:12:37,760 --> 01:12:40,080
Didn't I tell you that you don't need to cook?

858
01:12:40,080 --> 01:12:42,020
Luckily you only burned a pot.

859
01:12:42,020 --> 01:12:45,460
If you burn down this old house, I can't afford to repay.

860
01:12:45,460 --> 01:12:48,390
I just wanted to help.

861
01:12:51,700 --> 01:12:52,700
<i>Mom!</i>

862
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:55,600
Mom.

863
01:12:55,640 --> 01:12:58,080
How come you're home already?

864
01:12:58,080 --> 01:13:01,380
We took an airplane.<br>So we got here in no time.

865
01:13:01,380 --> 01:13:02,390
How are you, Auntie?

866
01:13:02,390 --> 01:13:05,690
Very good, very good.

867
01:13:05,690 --> 01:13:10,220
Right now I feel very happy, with two sons here,

868
01:13:10,220 --> 01:13:12,840
and two daughters-in-law!

869
01:13:16,040 --> 01:13:18,840
- Katy, are you cooking?<br>- Mhm.

870
01:13:18,840 --> 01:13:21,240
But... I made a mess.

871
01:13:21,240 --> 01:13:22,290
Let me help you.

872
01:13:22,290 --> 01:13:23,860
Great!

873
01:13:38,430 --> 01:13:42,900
<i>♫ I want to build a whole new different world. ♫ </i>

874
01:13:42,900 --> 01:13:48,240
<i>♫ I welcome you, welcome you to experience it. ♫ </i>

875
01:13:49,860 --> 01:13:52,500
Right now I feel very happy!

876
01:13:52,500 --> 01:13:57,030
I have two sons here, and two daughters-in-law!

877
01:14:00,230 --> 01:14:03,000
- Katy, are you cooking?<br>- Mhm.

878
01:14:03,000 --> 01:14:05,480
But... I made a mess.

879
01:14:05,480 --> 01:14:06,400
Let me help you.

880
01:14:06,400 --> 01:14:08,500
Great!

881
01:14:14,760 --> 01:14:16,040
I'll take care of this.

882
01:14:16,040 --> 01:14:19,650
Ok. You take care of it.

883
01:14:19,650 --> 01:14:20,940
Auntie. Be careful.

884
01:14:20,940 --> 01:14:22,610
<i>Ok!</i>

885
01:14:37,260 --> 01:14:40,030
William Yi. My mom looks very well.

886
01:14:40,030 --> 01:14:42,950
It looks like you do know how to take good care of her.

887
01:14:45,370 --> 01:14:50,710
Of course. I use the discipline of managing a company to<br>take care of your mom.

888
01:14:50,710 --> 01:14:54,030
I carefully select every thing she eats.

889
01:14:54,030 --> 01:14:57,650
I also cook the food attentively,<br>making sure it's healthy and nutritious.

890
01:14:57,650 --> 01:15:00,070
Really?

891
01:15:00,070 --> 01:15:02,810
Bro. When are you going back to work?

892
01:15:02,810 --> 01:15:04,670
You're having such a great time taking a vacation here,

893
01:15:04,670 --> 01:15:08,520
but I have to read documents everyday,<br>which almost drives me nuts.

894
01:15:10,760 --> 01:15:15,690
Actually... I like staying at Mei Village very much.

895
01:15:15,690 --> 01:15:17,630
What did you say?

896
01:15:19,510 --> 01:15:24,050
<i>Son! Go and bring me the biggest fish.</i>

897
01:15:24,050 --> 01:15:26,210
- I'll be right there!<br>- Ok!

898
01:15:33,060 --> 01:15:35,570
You've only stayed here a few days,

899
01:15:35,570 --> 01:15:39,350
and you already think you are my mom's son<br>just because you look like me?

900
01:15:39,350 --> 01:15:41,380
Please remember who you are.

901
01:15:41,380 --> 01:15:46,370
You haven't touched any fish for such a long time, <br>how would you know what kind of fish your mom wants?

902
01:15:46,370 --> 01:15:48,350
Give me a break.<br>Who am I?

903
01:15:48,350 --> 01:15:50,030
I am Liu Wen Bin.

904
01:15:50,030 --> 01:15:54,600
I am the best fish expert in Mei Village. Ok?

905
01:15:54,600 --> 01:15:57,310
That's hard to say.<br><i>(in Taiwanese)</i>

906
01:15:57,310 --> 01:16:00,640
That's right. I know you don't know how to speak Taiwanese.

907
01:16:00,640 --> 01:16:03,230
You can just speak Mandarin with me.

908
01:16:04,650 --> 01:16:06,300
I don't want to.<br><i>(in Taiwanese)</i>

909
01:16:08,410 --> 01:16:10,420
Whatever.

910
01:16:25,650 --> 01:16:27,320
Where are you taking me exactly?

911
01:16:27,320 --> 01:16:29,990
Your mom was going to teach me how to cook.

912
01:16:33,380 --> 01:16:36,090
Isn't the sea at Mei Village very beautiful?

913
01:16:36,090 --> 01:16:38,310
You can never get tired of looking at it.

914
01:16:39,730 --> 01:16:41,420
I know.

915
01:16:46,700 --> 01:16:53,300
Actually, this place has beautiful mountains, ocean, and fresh air.

916
01:16:53,900 --> 01:16:58,200
Anyone who lives here probably can stay very healthy. Right?

917
01:17:01,830 --> 01:17:06,490
By the way! Next month a new CEO will be elected.

918
01:17:06,490 --> 01:17:09,860
I probably can come back here to sell fish then.

919
01:17:09,860 --> 01:17:15,550
My life probably will be just like the way it used to be.

920
01:17:15,550 --> 01:17:17,440
That's really great.

921
01:17:18,940 --> 01:17:23,990
You... What exactly are you trying to say to me?

922
01:17:23,990 --> 01:17:28,360
Can it be... you're going to break up with me,

923
01:17:28,360 --> 01:17:30,820
and telling me "going back to<br>the way things were", that sort of things?

924
01:17:30,820 --> 01:17:33,560
No... no... That's not it.

925
01:17:33,560 --> 01:17:35,840
It's... Eh...

926
01:17:38,280 --> 01:17:43,140
I... I want to know if what you said<br>in front of the office building was true.

927
01:17:43,140 --> 01:17:45,620
What did I say?

928
01:17:45,620 --> 01:17:50,390
You... you said you were ready to move to Mei Village.

929
01:17:53,490 --> 01:17:55,420
That...?

930
01:17:56,400 --> 01:18:00,430
But... am I not living here right now?

931
01:18:01,500 --> 01:18:04,940
That's true.<br>But...

932
01:18:04,940 --> 01:18:08,030
Whenever I go back to Taipei, you also come with me.

933
01:18:08,030 --> 01:18:12,120
When I come live at Mei Village, you do too.

934
01:18:12,120 --> 01:18:16,720
This feel more like... traveling.

935
01:18:16,720 --> 01:18:20,320
Therefore... you don't like it?

936
01:18:20,320 --> 01:18:23,070
No... That's not what I mean.

937
01:18:23,070 --> 01:18:26,550
Then what do you mean?<br>You're making me very nervous.

938
01:18:26,550 --> 01:18:27,900
I'm very nervous too.

939
01:18:27,900 --> 01:18:29,460
What?

940
01:18:35,010 --> 01:18:36,280
Take this.

941
01:18:36,280 --> 01:18:38,100
What is this?

942
01:18:38,100 --> 01:18:40,460
Hold it.

943
01:18:40,460 --> 01:18:43,170
Where are you going? Hey!

944
01:18:43,170 --> 01:18:45,010
Hold onto it!

945
01:18:59,430 --> 01:19:04,350
Yi Xin. Will you marry me?

946
01:19:06,920 --> 01:19:09,670
What did you say?

947
01:19:11,600 --> 01:19:13,690
I'll speak louder!

948
01:19:18,960 --> 01:19:25,810
Yi Xin. Will you marry me?

949
01:19:36,470 --> 01:19:41,050
Speak louder! I can't hear you!

950
01:19:47,360 --> 01:19:49,370
Yi Xin!

951
01:19:52,860 --> 01:19:57,590
I love you! Let's get married!

952
01:19:57,590 --> 01:20:01,280
<i>♫ "Prince" is what they call<br>a young man of my generation. ♫ </i>

953
01:20:01,280 --> 01:20:04,390
<i>♫ Love is my DNA. ♫ </i>

954
01:20:04,390 --> 01:20:08,640
<i>♫ As long as my heart is beating like a drum,<br>I'll be able to fly high. ♫ </i>

955
01:20:08,640 --> 01:20:11,770
<i>♫ I want to go experience what the world has to offer<br>Say that's okay! ♫ </i>

